&lt;h2&gt;Dealing with broken symbolic links&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find broken symlinks and delete them&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_6e25e5fbacb94af7a51cf584b82b03c4-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$find&lt;/span&gt; -L /path/to/check -type l -delete
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;List them&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_338073996e8f4055960a7e34096ef49c-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$find&lt;/span&gt; -L /path -type l
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to delete them with confirmation first, do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_767007d326b4438c92ca35cccea2e24e-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$find&lt;/span&gt; -L /path -type l -exec rm -i &lt;span class="o"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt; +
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="creating-symbolik-links"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Creating symbolik links&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First cd into your directory and then indicate where your symlinks will point&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_52e8e011371448cda9950270537f9976-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$find&lt;/span&gt; /directory_where_yout_symlinks_are/ -maxdepth &lt;span class="m"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; -type d -exec ln -s  &lt;span class="o"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to update your existing symlinks, use the &lt;strong&gt;-f&lt;/strong&gt; option such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_a27b6896aeea40699d584a0673492eab-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$find&lt;/span&gt; /home/matt/workspace/unified_repos/erp_core/modules/ -maxdepth &lt;span class="m"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; -type d -exec ln -sf  &lt;span class="o"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div class="line-block"&gt;
&lt;div class="line"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
